<title>INDIA: India RBI allows FII buying in Infosys.</title>
<headline>India RBI allows FII buying in Infosys.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) said on Monday foreign institutional investors (FIIs) and other overseas bodies can buy up to 30 percent of the paid up capital of software firm Infosys Technologies.</p>
<p>The RBI said it wrote to authorised foreign exchange dealers informing them of its June 14 decision.</p>
<p>The decision follows Infosys passing a resolution at its June 7 annual general meeting raising investment limit for FIIs and overseas bodies to 30 percent.</p>
<p>FIIs and others earlier could not make fresh purchases in Infosys shares as their holding had touched the ceiling of 24 percent of the firm's capital.</p>
